<br>
I’m not familiar with the drops in this dungeon, as it was not itemized when I hunted there in Beta. The only boss I’ve killed during live is Scurceol Hyrde, who seems to drop about two items, and is the boss for the Ogre’s Might quest. Most of the bosses, with the exception of Scurceol and Orylle, can be taken down with only a few groups of players. <br>
 <br>
Scurceol Hyrde – One of the two main bosses of this dungeon. I would suggest about fifty players in order to be able to get a reasonable hit rate, because the level of the Nodes, which must be destroyed, is quite high. There are four Nodes, and while they are around, Scurceol is invulnerable. Pet spam and such are very effective. The nodes are stationary, and “fight” by throwing players into the air and using similar attacks. /stick will help minimize the falling damage you take. Once the four nodes are cleared, Scurceol can be harmed. <br>
 <br>
Beran the Supply Master – This ogre ignites the barrels around the room, causing sections of the room to explode and deal damage to players in that area. Not very difficult overall. <br>
 <br>
Morgus Urgalorg – This guy is an ogre wizard, who is training several other ogre wizards. No specific tactics seem to be necessary. <br>
 <br>
Orylle and Orshom Brong – Orshom and Orylle are both very powerful. Orshrom can generally be pulled first and fought separately, at least for a while, which makes things much easier. I’d suggest at least 50 or more players for this encounter. The fire that Orshom keeps lit can be put out by ice damage, which makes Orylle significantly less dangerous, since throwing players in the fire is one of her most frequent attacks. They both parry, so those tactics apply. Pet spam, Debuffs, etc. will probably be helpful for Orylle. Aggro management will be difficult, as Orylle has simply massive melee damage. <br>
 <br>
Fuladl – A named blob, which splits into several smaller blobs when attacked. The main monster has high defensive abilities, so the adds should be taken out first. <br>
 <br>
Deben se Gyende – A military commander, who commands several ogre fighters and mages. The AI in this encounter is excellent, and as such, it may be wise to Relog pull as many of his guards as possible before aggroing the boss and starting the main fight. <br>
 <br>
Fulafeallan - Another named blob, which splits into several smaller blobs when attacked. The main monster has high defensive abilities, so the adds should be taken out first. <br>
 <br>
Lurfos the Herald – He is a fairly strong attacker, who is capable of putting fire and ice effects onto his weapon for additional attacking power. Not horribly difficult, but interesting. <br>
 <br>
Ulor and Jehrog se Bysen – These are two ogres that work in tandem. Ulor casts offensive magic, while Jehrog melees. It would be wise to pet spam and attack Ulor first, then target Jehrog. <br>
 <br>
Krevo Ricik – Nothing really significant that I remember about this fight. <br>
 <br>
Drihten Elreden – This is an ogre friar, and he uses a significant number of styles. His students will stand by and watch, for the most part, so you don’t necessarily have to attack them immediately. Just be careful for potential adds, and you should be fine. <br>
